note_tweet.text:
⭕️Polkadot The most Dev friendly blockchain.

But why? 

We all know the words flexibility, scalability, but here is why Polkadot's ecosystem became top choice for building blockchain applications simplified:

⭕️Build faster with substrate
Polkadot is powered by Substrate. Its a modular framework that gives developers the opportunity to create costom blockchains but without starting from nothing. They can use pre built components which reduces development time drastically.

⭕️Cross-Chain communication "Talk to each other"
Say goodbye against expensive  and slow bridges that most traditional blockchains are using.  Polkadot lets different chains that are build on top of the Polkadot ecosystem communicate with each other. This means gaming rollups, DeFi apps or NFT platforms for example can interact without delaying the process. The so called "bottleneck"

⭕️ Shared Security with Security "In-Builds"
Most blockchains are asking the projects to require and build their own security. Polkadot does this differently. all chains can use the security from the main network. 

⭕️ Dev languages friendly and popular coding
Supporting multiple programming languages makes it accessible for all developers. This helps developers write and optimized blockchain applications without learning an whole new dev language. 

⭕️ Scalability 
Polkadot is using parallel processing (parachains) instead of making all their apps compete for block space like ETH. We all know when ETH's network is overloaded the gas price is high. The parallel design prevents this and making it ideal for high performance apps like gaming, AI or DeFi.

⭕️ Gaming and Web3 innovation
Polkadot is designed for the next generation of Web3 experiences. Polkadot can handle millions of transactions without having insanely high gas prices or stagnation. Which makes it ideal for Gaming. Think about Mythos or other parachains with an insanely high transaction count. combine them and you get millions and millions of transactions.

⭕️ Conclusion for Devs
Polkadot removes quite a few dev pains:
No need for expensive security validator networks
No complex scaling solutions are needed for them
No high gas prices or crazy and unpredictable fees
seamless multi chain compatibility with others.
